<subSubSection id="45499ED597798C26D6DB25B431F251A1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="CC84B10DA4A27D0C96C38A908C1AACD1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0B18ADBCE501B2EC8445DDA11E5F950E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Twining liana to c. 12 m in height; stems densely white-pubescent/floccose when young, glabrescent, somewhat woody when old. Leaves petiolate, 5-15 
<normalizedToken id="ECD69912112C74193BC6D5B05D76F307" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4.5-15 cm, suborbicular to subreniform, apex rounded to retuse, sometimes mucronate, base cordate with rounded auricles, adaxially pubescent to puberulent, grey-green, abaxially dotted with dark glands, densely and softly white-pubescent when young, somewhat glabrescent and becoming greenish; petioles 5-15 cm, densely pubescent. Inflorescence of solitary (rarely 2-3) pedunculate flowers from the leaf axils; peduncles 1-9 cm, pubescent, somewhat glabrescent; bracteoles caducous; secondary peduncles 2-3 mm, white tomentose; pedicels 8-20 mm, elongating to 2.5 cm in fruit, shortly white-tomentose; sepals subequal, pubescent, broadly ovate, suborbicular, 11-15 
<normalizedToken id="0AB24923DB8F249298631F6D2CA96E9B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
11 mm, markedly accrescent in fruit to 40 
<normalizedToken id="2794641F98B608CD50DE11CDD37D14E6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
35 mm and somewhat glabrescent; corolla 5.5-9 cm long, funnel-shaped, pink, pubescent towards the tips of the midpetaline bands; limb weakly lobed, 4.5-5 cm diam. Capsules 1.5-2 
<normalizedToken id="C50C6FF14A2C66D3050E6E50D3435C7D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-2.5 cm, compressed globose, indehiscent, enclosed by accrescent sepals; seeds ellipsoid, 9 
<normalizedToken id="88E4B015837611E75596C61D20D5E149" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6 mm, shortly but densely puberulent to subtomentose.
</paragraph>
